Heat the olive oil in a pan over a medium heat, add the leek and sautÃ© until softened. Add the garlic and fry for one minute.Add the white wine, turn up the heat and simmer for 2-3 minutes.Add the stock, double cream and capers and simmer for 3-4 minutes. Season, to taste, with salt and freshly ground black pepper.To serve, pour the soup into a serving bowl and garnish with chopped chives.